        ]
      ],
      "content": "The path narrows between stands of tall grass. The city noise fades. Up here there is only wind and the distant crackle of signal from the radio towers that crown the hill above you, their red lights beginning to blink as the afternoon dims.\n\nSomething about the light is different than you expected. Flatter. More specific."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
