      ],
      "content": "They are here.\n\nManoel and Miguel lie side by side in the grass, formal suits, waterproof coats, as though they dressed for something important. Which they did. The grass has already begun to grow back around them — three days of ordinary weather, ordinary time, while you were not here.\n\nEach of them wears a lead mask over their eyes. Crude things, hand-cut, shaped like sunglasses from another world. You have one like it in your coat pocket. You have had it there since August.\n\nA water bottle and a small notebook page lie in the grass. Nearby, a canvas bag. Manoel's shortwave radio sits propped against a rock, still on, still searching."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
