          "title",
          "Manoel"
        ],
        [
          "noun",
          "manoel",
          "manoel's body",
          "bodies",
          "body",
          "men",
          "them"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "Manoel lies on his left side, one arm extended as though pointing at something specific in the distance. His coat is buttoned to the top. You remember arguing with him once about whether any of this was real — the contacts, the signals, the belief that men with the right equipment could reach something beyond ordinary frequency. He said: *what is real is what you are willing to wait for.* He looks like he is still waiting."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
