        ],
        [
          "noun",
          "miguel",
          "miguel's body"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "Miguel. The waitress at the bar described him as very nervous. You believe that. Miguel was always very nervous — had been since you were teenagers repairing radios in his father's shop, always checking his watch, always a few seconds ahead of whatever was happening, anticipating the next moment before this one had finished. You wonder if that is still true. If somewhere he is still nervous. Still checking."
    },
