        ],
        [
          "noun",
          "masks",
          "their masks",
          "lead masks"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "Hand-cut lead, roughly shaped to cover the eyes. Crude wire holds them in place. They are not comfortable — you can see that. They were not meant for comfort. They were meant for protection. Against what kind of light you still do not know. Against what specific frequency of the visible. You put your hand in your coat pocket and feel the edge of yours."
    },
