        ],
        [
          "sound",
          "30078:<PUBKEY>:vintem:sound:wind-ambient",
          "ambient",
          "0.6"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "The top of Vintém Hill. The towers are close enough to touch, their red lights now blinking regularly against a sky that has gone fully dark at the edges and still holds a pale yellow band above the horizon where the sun was.\n\nThe static from the shortwave below has become something else up here — not cleaner, but more present. More directional. As though it knows something about the specific angle of your attention.\n\nYou are at the agreed place. The note said 18:30. The window is open.\n\nYou can wait."
    },
