        ],
        [
          "title",
          "A Kerb in Niterói"
        ],
        [
          "exit",
          "out"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "You walked down the hill. You found a telephone outside a pharmacy three blocks from the bus stop. You told them there were two bodies on Vintém Hill and gave them the path directions and then you hung up because you did not know what else to say.\n\nNow you sit on a kerb in the dark. Your coat pocket is still heavy. The mask is still in it. You did not leave it on the hill. You do not know why.\n\nA police car will come. You will tell them you are a friend. You will tell them you found them this way. Both things are true.\n\nThe signal, if there was one, came without you. Or it did not come at all. Either way, you will not know. That is the condition you have chosen: safety, and not knowing.\n\nThe kerb is cold. You wait for headlights."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
        [
          "d",
          "vintem:place:ending-witness"
        ],
        [
          "t",
          "vintem"
        ],
        [
          "type",
          "place"
        ],
        [
          "title",
          "The Site, Morning"
        ],
        [
          "exit",
          "stay"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "You stayed. You did not complete the ritual. You did not call the police. You sat between them through the night, the shortwave still running, the static cycling through its almost-patterns, the city lights below going out one district at a time and then coming back with the dawn.\n\nYou do not know if sitting here means anything. It felt like the only honest option. You owed them a witness. Nobody else was going to come.\n\nThe boy arrives at mid-morning, string trailing behind him, kite not yet airborne. He comes over the ridge and stops.\n\nHe looks at Manoel. He looks at Miguel. He looks at you — sitting upright between them, mask in your lap, alive in the obvious way that they are not.\n\nHe runs.\n\nYou let him. He will bring people. You will still be here."
    },
