        [
          "title",
          "The Signal"
        ],
        [
          "exit",
          "down"
        ]
      ],
      "content": "You wait.\n\nThe static from below resolves — slowly, the way a signal finds its station — into something that is almost a tone, and then is a tone, ascending, precise, coming from a direction that is not any direction you have a word for.\n\nThe lead mask covers your eyes. The darkness behind it is complete and absolute and, after a moment, is not darkness.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nThe case was never solved. The cause of death was never established. No trace of the capsules was found. The lead masks were logged as evidence and later lost.\n\nManoel Pereira da Cruz and Miguel José Viana were buried in Campos dos Goytacazes in September 1966. The shortwave was returned to Miguel's family. His sister kept it. She said it still worked.\n\nSergio is not in any record."
    },
    {
      "kind": 30078,
      "tags": [
